org.greencheek.processio.service.usage
Interface AccumulatedAverageKbPerSecondCalculator

All Known Implementing Classes:
PrimitiveBasedAccumulatedAverageKBPerSecondCalculator
public interface AccumulatedAverageKbPerSecondCalculator

Given a starting time in the past and a current timestamp, and given the number representing the amount of bytes used by the process between those two times; the implementing class will work out the amount of Kb (Kilobytes) per second that equates to.

Method Detail

getKbPerSecond

double getKbPerSecond(long sinceTimeStamp,
                      long currentTimeStamp,
                      long currentBytes)
Returns the amount of kb per second has been processed/performed between the two time stamps

Parameters:
sinceTimeStamp - The first time stamp (usually the time the jvm started)
currentTimeStamp - A recent time stamp (greater than the sinceTimeStamp)
currentBytes - The amount of io that the process has consumed in total since the start of it
Returns:
The amount of IO that has occurred in kb per second between the two times.
